ription":"Unfair agreements between businesses: price-fixing, cartels and reporting unfair practices to the OFT","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Any agreement that restricts competition in the UK or elsewhere in the <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> may be illegal. You can report anti-competitive agreements to the Office of Fair Trading (<abbr title=\"Office of Fair Trading\">OFT</abbr>).</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Examples of agreements which can be anti-competitive include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>price-fixing (agreeing with any other business on a minimum price to sell goods or services at)</li>\n  <li>limiting production to drive up prices</li>\n  <li>if 2 contracts are put out to tender, agreeing with your competitor to only bid on 1 each</li>\n  <li>agreeing not to sell to a competitor&rsquo;s customers or compete against them in a certain area</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If 2 or more competitors make agreements like these, it might constitute a ‘cartel’. </p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s more information about fair competition and cartels on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.oft.gov.uk/business-advice/competing/\" title=\"Competing fairly\"><abbr title=\"Office of Fair Trading\">OFT</abbr> website.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Informal agreements</h2>\n\n<p>An anti-competitive agreement doesn&rsquo;t have to be formal, written down or even discussed to be illegal. </p>\n\n<p>&lsquo;Shared understandings&rsquo;, &lsquo;gentleman&rsquo;s agreements&rsquo; and &lsquo;concerted practices&rsquo; that clearly restrict competition can also be illegal. Concerted practices are where businesses cooperate without actually reaching an agreement or decision.</p>\n\n<h2>Penalties</h2>\n\n<p>Your business could be sued, fined or prosecuted if it enters into an anti-competitive agreement. If you enter into a cartel agreement you could receive an unlimited fine or a prison sentence of up to 5 years.</p>\n\n<p>Your business could be fined up to 10% of its turnover and company directors could be disqualified.</p>\n\n<h2>Report anti-competitive agreements</h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Office of Fair Trading\">OFT</abbr> investigates claims of anti-competitive agreements. If you suspect a business is involved in an anti-competitive agreement, you can <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.oft.gov.uk/advice_and_resources-old/small_businesses/competing/suspicious\" title=\"Report suspicious behaviour\">report suspicious behaviour.</a></p>\n\n","alternative_title":"Competition law: unfair and anti-competitive agreements"},"tags":[{"title":"Sale of goods and services and data protection","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Fsale-goods-services-data.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes regulations for online retailers, offering credit and Trading Standards","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Fsale-goods-services-data","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/sale-goods-services-data"},"parent":{"title":"Businesses and self-employed","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/find-local-trading-standards-office.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/find-local-trading-standards-office","title":"Find your local Trading Standards office","format":"transaction","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:22:26+00:00"}]},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/contracts-finder.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder","title":"Contracts Finder","format":"transaction","updated_at":"2012-11-27T16:38:13+00:00","details":{"need_id":"B1046","business_proposition":true,"description"